ch.hevs.cloudio.endpoint

Class CloudioAdLibObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.hevs.cloudio.endpoint.CloudioObject
      • ch.hevs.cloudio.endpoint.CloudioAdLibObject

  • public class CloudioAdLibObject
extends CloudioObject
    The CloudioAdLibObject class allows you to create the structure of a cloud.iO node at runtime in contrast to the static model used by the CloudioObject class. TODO: Example.

        Adds a new attribute of the given type (class) and the given name to the object. Note that if there is already an attribute with the given name present or the type of the attribute is invalid, an exception will be thrown.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Attribute's type.
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the attribute to add.
        type - Type of the attribute to add.
        constraint - Attribute's constraint.
        initialValue - Initial value for the attribute.
        Returns:
        Reference to the newly instantiated attribute.
        Throws:
        DuplicateNamedItemException - If there already exists an attribute with the given name.
        InvalidCloudioAttributeException - If the type of the attribute is not supported.
        CloudioAttributeInitializationException - If the attribute could not be initialized.
        CloudioAttributeConstraintException - If the attribute can not be initialized (constraint).

      • declareConformance

        public void declareConformance(java.lang.String dataClass)
        Declares conformance of the object for a given data class. Note that a cloud.io objects can only declare conformance for exactly one data class, it you try to declare a second conformance , a runtime exception will be thrown. Additionally this method can only be called before the object is part of an endpoint structure.
        Parameters:
        dataClass - Data class the object conforms to.
